&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is with Kernow Health CIC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kernow Health CIC are looking to recruit a programme manager to support the Head of Integrated Urgent Care in the operational delivery of a high quality and effective IUCS Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will focus both on the core delivery of the IUCS service and supporting the roll out of an exciting new digital care plan strategy for Cornwall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a highly motivated, enthusiastic and flexible individual, with excellent organisational skills and comprehensive knowledge and experience of business management functions and systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a busy and varied role, one which requires the post holder to have a flexible approach and a calm, professional manner. The ability to work accurately whilst multi-tasking is essential. The right candidate should have a strong administrative background with experience of supporting senior managers/directors and have worked in a busy, demanding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills and be able to work confidently under pressure. You will be required to use your own initiative, have an ability to prioritise work and be able to work collaboratively as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kieran Bignell on 01872 222400&lt;/p&gt;
